clinical_study.brief_title: Safety and Tolerability of TWP-201 in Healthy Female Subjects
clinical_study.official_title: A Randomized, Double-blind, Placebo-controlled, Single Dose, Escalation, Phase I Clinical Trial to Evaluate the Safety and Tolerability of TWP-201 in Healthy Female Subjects

brief_summary.textblock: This study is a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, single dose, escalation, phase I clinical trial to evaluate the safety and tolerability of recombinant human follicle stimulating hormone Fc fusion protein injection (TWP-201) in healthy female subjects. The objective of the trial is to evaluate the safety and tolerability of TWP-201 in healthy female subjects.

study_design_info.masking: Quadruple (Participant, Care Provider, Investigator, Outcomes Assessor)

primary_outcome.measure: Incidence of adverse events, serious adverse and abnormal laboratory values event (defined by the Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events version 5.0 (CTCAE V5.0)).

secondary_outcome.measure: Maximum measured plasma concentration (Cmax) of TWP-201;
Time to maximum plasma concentration (Tmax) of TWP-201;

secondary_outcome.description: Determination of serum concentrations of FSH, E2 and LH after dosing.
The number of follicles after dosing. The size of follicles after dosing.
Blood samples will be collected from subjects post treatment for assessment to detect the presence of anti-drug antibodies and neutralizing antibodies.

facility.name: West China Second University Hospital, Sichuan University
